ATS = Autotransformer Station
Provides connection between +25kV contact wire circuits and -25kV trackside feeder wires via 1 or more centre tapped autotransformers, typically only via load-break isolators rather than circuit breakers

tags.name: Reading ATFS
tags.note: Lines here are normally supplied by incoming circuits from Didcot (Foxhall) ATFS. In case of an outage there, Reading can supply this area from a 17km 25/0/-25 cable along the Reading-Basingstoke line from Holly Cross ATFS which connects to Bramley 400kV.

tags.name: Bushey Feeder Station
tags.note: Supplied by 25kV underground cables from Elstree 400kV National Grid transmission substation. Normally feeds the railway from North Wembley MPTSC to Bourne End MPATS excluding the adjacent 750V DC 3rd rail line from Euston to Watford Junction.

tags.name: Slough ATS

tags.name: Hayes SATS / FS
tags.note:
SATS = Sectioning Auto-transformer Station
This was the 132/25 feeder station (FS) for the Heathrow Express system (1998 to 2017). Apparently that original grid connection is still available although either not in regular use or only feeds airport branch.
